text: We're moving up the charts!

I will be out for the afternoon, but the scripts are solid now, so <@U05FU0HPZ9T> can just do the onboarding, once we have their validator id. Steps:

1. `git pull git@github.com:DLC-link/canton-billing-scripts.git`
2. copy `[MAINNET] Canton Billings Scripts Env` from 1Pass>Engineering into `.env`
3. Rewrite the `input.json` file with the two licenses for trade13. Input their validatorId, and update the `partyIdHint` fields
4. `sudo chmod +x main.sh`
5. `./main.sh`
6. Watch it fly
7. Put the resulting partyIds into the gsheet. This is independent of the scripts actually, it will always be for example: `[CLIENT[-MINTER]::[MAINNET-NAMESPACE]`, so `round13::1220409a9fcc5ff6422e29ab978c22c004dde33202546b4bcbde24b25b85353366c2` and `round13-minter::1220409a9fcc5ff6422e29ab978c22c004dde33202546b4bcbde24b25b85353366c2`   (in fact we could just prefill these in the gsheet, but maybe better to wait until they are set up)
8. Update backend env users credentials, using the output files of the scripts. One of them will have the username/pwds of these new accounts
9. $$$
